# Native binaries are staged into these packages at build time
# (build.bat / build.sh / build-mac.sh) and published from CI.
# They are build artifacts and must never be committed. Only the
# package manifests and READMEs are tracked here.
#
# Note: this ignore rule is a source-control hygiene measure only. It does
# NOT define the npm publish boundary — each package.json carries an explicit
# "files" allowlist of the exact binaries it ships, so stray artifacts (logs,
# .pdb symbols, .env, prior *.tgz) are never published even though they are
# untracked. A "prepack" guard in each manifest additionally refuses to pack a
# package whose primary binary was not staged.
**
!*/
!*/package.json
!*/README.md
!.gitignore
